text: Liu Yanhan (; born 19 January 1993 in Liaoning) is a female Chinese volleyball player. She won the 2013 FIVB Women's U23 Volleyball World Championship. ==Clubs== * Army ==Awards== * 2010 U18 Asian Championship – "Best Spiker" * 2010 U18 Asian Championship – "Best Blocker" * 2010 U20 Asian Championship – "Best Spiker" * 2010 U20 Asian Championship – "Most Valuable Player" * 2014 Asian Cup – "Best Outside Spikers" * 2014–15 Chinese League – "Most Valuable Player" * 2015 U23 Asian Championship – "Most Valuable Player" * 2015 U23 Asian Championship – "Best Outside Spiker" * 2016 Asian Club Championship – "Best Outside Spiker" * 2018 Asian Cup – "Most Valuable Player" * 2019 FIVB Nations League – "Best Outside Spiker" ==References== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Chinese women's volleyball players Category:Volleyball players from Liaoning Category:Asian Games medalists in volleyball Category:Volleyball players at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Asian Games silver medalists for China Category:Medalists at the 2014 Asian Games Category:Wing spikers
title: Liu Yanhan
